question: (abt andi mack) does no one else think that the whole kira-tj thing could be leading up to tj coming out/confessing that he likes cyrus?? kira made him do the costume so he wouldn't be outed and he could possibly confess to cyrus whole apologising or at least hint that kira knew something that he didn't want cyrus or anyone else to know (i.e. he's gay/has a crush on cyrus)??? is no one else thinking this?
answer:
no i’m pretty sure literally everyone is saying this nfjsjfjs

i don’t think it’s fair that people are saying she threatened to out him cause as far we know she literally didn’t do that unless it happened off screen but the implications in that scene were definitely at least supposed to have homophobic undertones with the oh so you’d rather dress with a BOY than a GIRL, which is why tj was completely excited and set in his decision up until that last line where you can see his face change.

summary: i don’t really think that kira is homophobic. i also don’t really think she wants to date tj. i think she was manipulating tj so...
body: i don’t really think that kira is homophobic. i also don’t really think she wants to date tj. i think she was manipulating tj so she could get to cyrus, which could in turn piss off buffy. cyrus and buffy are best friends, so when cyrus is hurt then buffy is hurt too. kira saw an opportunity to use tj and cyrus’ relationship to piss buffy off and make her life harder, so she took it. i don’t think it has too much to do with homophobia, just more of the fact that she’s blinded by her hatred for buffy and doesn’t really care if she manipulates tj and cyrus in the process of pissing buffy off.

summary: I know everyone’s talking about how they feel bad for tyrus, but you know who really got screwed over? Andi. In 20 minutes, we...
body:
I know everyone’s talking about how they feel bad for tyrus, but you know who really got screwed over? Andi. In 20 minutes, we saw:

  • Andi watching one of her best friends get back into a formerly toxic relationship with his ex.
  • Amber and Jonah constantly coming to Andi to vent about their relationship, without so much as asking how she was doing.
  • Andi coming home to find out her parents are breaking off their engagement – something she’s eagerly helped plan for months.
  • Andi showing up to school the next day, still upset about her parents, only to find out her two best friends are bailing on the one thing she was looking forward to.

Yeah, I know sometimes Andi is over dramatic and self centered, but her reaction in this episode was totally justified. She really didn’t deserve any of that.
